'''''Posankka''''' is a [[statue]] located in [[Turku]], [[Finland]]. The statue, which is located near the campus area of the [[University of Turku]] and the [[Turku Student Village]], represents a hybrid between a [[marzipan pig]] ("possu") and a [[rubber duck]] ("ankka"). It is a pink animal with a duck's lower body and a pig's head.<ref name="Gullichsen">{{cite web|title=Alvar Gullichsen (1961&ndash;) Posankka|url=http://www.turku.fi/public/?contentid=62348&nodeid=13067|publisher=Wäinö Aaltosen Museo|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928173014/http://www.turku.fi/public/?contentid=62348&nodeid=13067|archivedate=2011-09-28|df=}}</ref>

The statue was designed by [[Alvar Gullichsen]] in 1999 when it was placed floating in the Aurajoki river in Turku. The statue has stood at its current location since 2001.<ref name="Gullichsen" />

Every winter, a [[Santa Claus]] hat is put on ''Posankka''{{'}}s head, <ref>{{cite web|title=Hiippalakki kruunasi Posankan joulun|language=Finnish|url=http://www.ts.fi/online/kotimaa/182277.html|publisher=Turun Sanomat|author=Heli Peltoniemi|date=2010-12-17|accessdate=2010-12-17|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717045113/http://www.ts.fi/online/kotimaa/182277.html|archivedate=2011-07-17|df=}}</ref> and on [[Walpurgis Night]] it is capped with a Finnish student cap<ref>http://www.ts.fi/uutiset/paikalliset/337808/Posankan+vappu+alkoi+etukenossa</ref>.

